OwnerString.name: OwnerString
OwnerString.description: This data type is used to model an administratively assigned name of the owner of a resource. This information is taken from the NVT ASCII character set. It is suggested that this name contain one or more of the following: ASCII form of the manager station's transport address, management station name (e.g., domain name), network management personnel's name, location, or phone number. In some cases the agent itself will be the owner of an entry. In these cases, this string shall be set to a string starting with 'agent'.

tokenRingMLStatsTable.name: tokenRingMLStatsTable
tokenRingMLStatsTable.description: A list of Mac-Layer Token Ring statistics entries.

tokenRingMLStatsEntry.name: tokenRingMLStatsEntry
tokenRingMLStatsEntry.description: A collection of Mac-Layer statistics kept for a particular Token Ring interface.

tokenRingMLStatsIndex.name: tokenRingMLStatsIndex
tokenRingMLStatsIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies this tokenRingMLStats entry.

tokenRingMLStatsDataSource.name: tokenRingMLStatsDataSource
tokenRingMLStatsDataSource.description: This object identifies the source of the data that this tokenRingMLStats entry is configured to analyze. This source can be any tokenRing interface on this device. In order to identify a particular interface, this object shall identify the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in MIB-II [3], for the desired interface. For example, if an entry were to receive data from interface #1, this object would be set to ifIndex.1. The statistics in this group reflect all error reports on the local network segment attached to the identified interface. This object may not be modified if the associated tokenRingMLStatsStatus object is equal to valid(1).

tokenRingMLStatsDropEvents.name: tokenRingMLStatsDropEvents
tokenRingMLStatsDropEvents.description: The total number of events in which packets were dropped by the probe due to lack of resources. Note that this number is not necessarily the number of packets dropped; it is just the number of times this condition has been detected. This value is the same as the corresponding tokenRingPStatsDropEvents.

tokenRingMLStatsMacOctets.name: tokenRingMLStatsMacOctets
tokenRingMLStatsMacOctets.description: The total number of octets of data in MAC packets (excluding those that were not good frames) received on the network (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

tokenRingMLStatsMacPkts.name: tokenRingMLStatsMacPkts
tokenRingMLStatsMacPkts.description: The total number of MAC packets (excluding packets that were not good frames) received.

tokenRingMLStatsRingPurgeEvents.name: tokenRingMLStatsRingPurgeEvents
tokenRingMLStatsRingPurgeEvents.description: The total number of times that the ring enters the ring purge state from normal ring state. The ring purge state that comes in response to the claim token or beacon state is not counted.

tokenRingMLStatsRingPurgePkts.name: tokenRingMLStatsRingPurgePkts
tokenRingMLStatsRingPurgePkts.description: The total number of ring purge MAC packets detected by probe.

tokenRingMLStatsBeaconEvents.name: tokenRingMLStatsBeaconEvents
tokenRingMLStatsBeaconEvents.description: The total number of times that the ring enters a beaconing state (beaconFrameStreamingState, beaconBitStreamingState, beaconSetRecoveryModeState, or beaconRingSignalLossState) from a non-beaconing state. Note that a change of the source address of the beacon packet does not constitute a new beacon event.

tokenRingMLStatsBeaconTime.name: tokenRingMLStatsBeaconTime
tokenRingMLStatsBeaconTime.description: The total amount of time that the ring has been in the beaconing state.

tokenRingMLStatsBeaconPkts.name: tokenRingMLStatsBeaconPkts
tokenRingMLStatsBeaconPkts.description: The total number of beacon MAC packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsClaimTokenEvents.name: tokenRingMLStatsClaimTokenEvents
tokenRingMLStatsClaimTokenEvents.description: The total number of times that the ring enters the claim token state from normal ring state or ring purge state. The claim token state that comes in response to a beacon state is not counted.

tokenRingMLStatsClaimTokenPkts.name: tokenRingMLStatsClaimTokenPkts
tokenRingMLStatsClaimTokenPkts.description: The total number of claim token MAC packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsNAUNChanges.name: tokenRingMLStatsNAUNChanges
tokenRingMLStatsNAUNChanges.description: The total number of NAUN changes detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsLineErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsLineErrors
tokenRingMLStatsLineErrors.description: The total number of line errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsInternalErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsInternalErrors
tokenRingMLStatsInternalErrors.description: The total number of adapter internal errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsBurstErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsBurstErrors
tokenRingMLStatsBurstErrors.description: The total number of burst errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsACErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsACErrors
tokenRingMLStatsACErrors.description: The total number of AC (Address Copied) errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsAbortErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsAbortErrors
tokenRingMLStatsAbortErrors.description: The total number of abort delimiters reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsLostFrameErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsLostFrameErrors
tokenRingMLStatsLostFrameErrors.description: The total number of lost frame errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsCongestionErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsCongestionErrors
tokenRingMLStatsCongestionErrors.description: The total number of receive congestion errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsFrameCopiedErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsFrameCopiedErrors
tokenRingMLStatsFrameCopiedErrors.description: The total number of frame copied errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsFrequencyErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsFrequencyErrors
tokenRingMLStatsFrequencyErrors.description: The total number of frequency errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsTokenErrors.name: tokenRingMLStatsTokenErrors
tokenRingMLStatsTokenErrors.description: The total number of token errors reported in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsSoftErrorReports.name: tokenRingMLStatsSoftErrorReports
tokenRingMLStatsSoftErrorReports.description: The total number of soft error report frames detected by the probe.

tokenRingMLStatsRingPollEvents.name: tokenRingMLStatsRingPollEvents
tokenRingMLStatsRingPollEvents.description: The total number of ring poll events detected by the probe (i.e. the number of ring polls initiated by the active monitor that were detected).

tokenRingMLStatsOwner.name: tokenRingMLStatsOwner
tokenRingMLStatsOwner.description: The entity that configured this entry and is therefore using the resources assigned to it.

tokenRingMLStatsStatus.name: tokenRingMLStatsStatus
tokenRingMLStatsStatus.description: The status of this tokenRingMLStats entry.

tokenRingMLHistoryEntry.name: tokenRingMLHistoryEntry
tokenRingMLHistoryEntry.description: A collection of Mac-Layer statistics kept for a particular Token Ring interface.

tokenRingMLHistoryIndex.name: tokenRingMLHistoryIndex
tokenRingMLHistoryIndex.description: The history of which this entry is a part. The history identified by a particular value of this index is the same history as identified by the same value of historyControlIndex.

tokenRingMLHistorySampleIndex.name: tokenRingMLHistorySampleIndex
tokenRingMLHistorySampleIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the particular Mac-Layer sample this entry represents among all Mac-Layer samples associated with the same historyControlEntry. This index starts at 1 and increases by one as each new sample is taken.

tokenRingMLHistoryIntervalStart.name: tokenRingMLHistoryIntervalStart
tokenRingMLHistoryIntervalStart.description: The value of sysUpTime at the start of the interval over which this sample was measured. If the probe keeps track of the time of day, it should start the first sample of the history at a time such that when the next hour of the day begins, a sample is started at that instant. Note that following this rule may require the probe to delay collecting the first sample of the history, as each sample must be of the same interval. Also note that the sample which is currently being collected is not accessible in this table until the end of its interval.

tokenRingMLHistoryDropEvents.name: tokenRingMLHistoryDropEvents
tokenRingMLHistoryDropEvents.description: The total number of events in which packets were dropped by the probe due to lack of resources during this sampling interval. Note that this number is not necessarily the number of packets dropped, it is just the number of times this condition has been detected.

tokenRingMLHistoryMacPkts.name: tokenRingMLHistoryMacPkts

tokenRingMLHistoryRingPurgeEvents.name: tokenRingMLHistoryRingPurgeEvents

tokenRingMLHistoryRingPurgePkts.name: tokenRingMLHistoryRingPurgePkts

tokenRingMLHistoryBeaconEvents.name: tokenRingMLHistoryBeaconEvents

Note that a change of the source address of the beacon packet does not constitute a new beacon event.

tokenRingMLHistoryBeaconPkts.name: tokenRingMLHistoryBeaconPkts

tokenRingMLHistoryClaimTokenEvents.description: The total number of times that the ring enters the claim token state from normal ring state or ring purge state during this sampling interval. The claim token state that comes from the beacon state is not counted.

ringStationControlTable.name: ringStationControlTable
ringStationControlTable.description: A list of ringStation table control entries.

ringStationControlEntry.name: ringStationControlEntry
ringStationControlEntry.description: A list of parameters that set up the discovery of stations on a particular interface and the collection of statistics about these stations.

ringStationControlIfIndex.name: ringStationControlIfIndex
ringStationControlIfIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the interface on this remote network monitoring device from which ringStation data is collected. The interface identified by a particular value of this object is the same interface as identified by the same value of the ifIndex object, defined in MIB- II [3].

ringStationControlTableSize.name: ringStationControlTableSize
ringStationControlTableSize.description: The number of ringStationEntries in the ringStationTable associated with this ringStationControlEntry.

ringStationControlActiveStations.name: ringStationControlActiveStations
ringStationControlActiveStations.description: The number of active ringStationEntries in the ringStationTable associated with this ringStationControlEntry.

ringStationControlRingState.name: ringStationControlRingState
ringStationControlRingState.description: The current status of this ring.

ringStationControlBeaconSender.name: ringStationControlBeaconSender
ringStationControlBeaconSender.description: The address of the sender of the last beacon frame received by the probe on this ring. If no beacon frames have been received, this object shall be equal to six octets of zero.

ringStationControlBeaconNAUN.name: ringStationControlBeaconNAUN
ringStationControlBeaconNAUN.description: The address of the NAUN in the last beacon frame received by the probe on this ring. If no beacon frames have been received, this object shall be equal to six octets of zero.

ringStationControlActiveMonitor.name: ringStationControlActiveMonitor
ringStationControlActiveMonitor.description: The address of the Active Monitor on this segment. If this address is unknown, this object shall be equal to six octets of zero.

ringStationControlOrderChanges.name: ringStationControlOrderChanges
ringStationControlOrderChanges.description: The number of add and delete events in the ringStationOrderTable optionally associated with this ringStationControlEntry.

ringStationControlOwner.name: ringStationControlOwner
ringStationControlOwner.description: The entity that configured this entry and is therefore using the resources assigned to it.

ringStationControlStatus.name: ringStationControlStatus
ringStationControlStatus.description: The status of this ringStationControl entry. If this object is not equal to valid(1), all associated entries in the ringStationTable shall be deleted by the agent.

ringStationTable.name: ringStationTable
ringStationTable.description: A list of ring station entries. An entry will exist for each station that is now or has previously been detected as physically present on this ring.

ringStationEntry.name: ringStationEntry
ringStationEntry.description: A collection of statistics for a particular station that has been discovered on a ring monitored by this device.

ringStationIfIndex.name: ringStationIfIndex
ringStationIfIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the interface on this remote network monitoring device on which this station was detected. The interface identified by a particular value of this object is the same interface as identified by the same value of the ifIndex object, defined in MIB-II [3].

ringStationMacAddress.name: ringStationMacAddress
ringStationMacAddress.description: The physical address of this station.

ringStationLastNAUN.name: ringStationLastNAUN
ringStationLastNAUN.description: The physical address of last known NAUN of this station.

ringStationStationStatus.name: ringStationStationStatus
ringStationStationStatus.description: The status of this station on the ring.

ringStationLastEnterTime.name: ringStationLastEnterTime
ringStationLastEnterTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this station last entered the ring. If the time is unknown, this value shall be zero.

ringStationLastExitTime.name: ringStationLastExitTime
ringStationLastExitTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the probe detected that this station last exited the ring. If the time is unknown, this value shall be zero.

ringStationDuplicateAddresses.name: ringStationDuplicateAddresses
ringStationDuplicateAddresses.description: The number of times this station experienced a duplicate address error.

ringStationInLineErrors.name: ringStationInLineErrors
ringStationInLineErrors.description: The total number of line errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

ringStationOutLineErrors.name: ringStationOutLineErrors
ringStationOutLineErrors.description: The total number of line errors reported in error reporting packets sent by the nearest active downstream neighbor of this station and detected by the probe.

ringStationInternalErrors.name: ringStationInternalErrors
ringStationInternalErrors.description: The total number of adapter internal errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

ringStationInBurstErrors.name: ringStationInBurstErrors
ringStationInBurstErrors.description: The total number of burst errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

ringStationOutBurstErrors.name: ringStationOutBurstErrors
ringStationOutBurstErrors.description: The total number of burst errors reported in error reporting packets sent by the nearest active downstream neighbor of this station and detected by the probe.

ringStationACErrors.name: ringStationACErrors
ringStationACErrors.description: The total number of AC (Address Copied) errors reported in error reporting packets sent by the nearest active downstream neighbor of this station and detected by the probe.

ringStationAbortErrors.name: ringStationAbortErrors
ringStationAbortErrors.description: The total number of abort delimiters reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

ringStationLostFrameErrors.name: ringStationLostFrameErrors
ringStationLostFrameErrors.description: The total number of lost frame errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

ringStationCongestionErrors.name: ringStationCongestionErrors
ringStationCongestionErrors.description: The total number of receive congestion errors reported by this station in error reporting packets detected by the probe.

ringStationFrameCopiedErrors.name: ringStationFrameCopiedErrors
